just_use pain_rank.py

# label: SPIKE (code-analysis tool)
# role: agent tool — rank source files by composite pain score

Cheap quantitative proxies for "probably annoying to work
in," rank-normalized across files and combined as a weighted
sum. Higher = more painful.

## Metrics

- `size` — total lines (tangled concerns).
- `todo_count` — TODO/FIXME/HACK/XXX markers (self-labeled
  pain).
- `churn` — commits touching the file (bug magnet / hot
  spot).
- `err_density` — `if err != nil` lines / total lines (Go
  boilerplate).
- `escape_density` — `html.EscapeString`-like calls (view
  boilerplate).

## Status (TENTATIVE)

Labeled SPIKE; run it occasionally as a triage lens. Haven't
validated that current weights produce useful rankings on the
post-refactor tree — the original balance was tuned against
an older layout. Treat the output as a *direction*, not a
scoreboard.

## Surface

- `python3 tools/pain_rank.py` — rank all source files.
- `--top N` — show top N.
- `--weights KEY=VAL,...` — override weight balance.

Filters out generated files, vendored trees, `.min.js`, and
tests by default.

## Pointers

- Related tool: `tools/feature_weight.py` (different lens,
  feature-scoped rather than global).
